node.text:
Repost from @theshaderoomteens
•
#TSRTPositiveImages: 
@FashionNovaCares and #TheShadeRoom @NoIGAngelica donate $100K to @Peace4Kids to support their ROCMove initiative. @ROCMove is a multigenerational initiative led predominantly by women and girls with lived experience in foster care. It's designed to uplift media and interactive training to highlight stories of power, transformation and resilience, evolving our country’s negative perception of foster care. For 22 years Peace4Kids has been fueled by the idea that youth in foster care deserve equitable opportunities to create community and connect with people who authentically care for them. Peace4Kids honors the intergenerational voices of foster care and provides the tools to navigate past trauma, embrace the future and thrive.  #NationalFosterCareMonth #FashionNovaCares

node.title: Why The Foster Care System Needs Us

node.text:
Colonoscopy!

Yeppers it is #recommended, average-risk adults should begin #colorectalcancer #screening at age 45 (I just turned 45).

Colon cancer is the #most #common type of gastrointestinal cancer. 

Because early-stage colon cancer is typically asymptomatic, screening plays a major role in the diagnosis of curable cancerous lesions, as well as the detection of precancerous lesions.

Symptoms include:

Iron-deficiency anemia, rectal 🩸 bleeding, abdominal pain, change in bowel habits, diarrhea, abdominal mass

To lower your risk: 
1. 🚭 Don’t smoke
2. Eat lots of vegetables, fruits, and whole grains.
3.Eat less red meat (beef, pork, or lamb) and avoid processed meats (hot dogs and lunch meats).
4.Get regular exercise. 
5. Take control of your weight. Being overweight or obese increases your risk of getting and dying from cancer.
6. Avoid alcohol. Alcohol use has been linked with a higher risk of colorectal cancer.  It is best to not drink alcohol. But if you do (like I do :-) the American Cancer Society recommends no more than 2 drinks a day for men and 1 drink a day for women. A single drink equals 12 ounces of beer, 5 ounces of wine or 1½ ounces of 80-proof distilled spirits (hard liquor). 

Encourage your #lovedones 45 years old and older to schedule their colonoscopy today!

#DrContessa #married2med #preventivemedicine #fyp #selfcare

Happy 89th Birthday To Ms. Luellen 💗

Wish I had my grandmas(or even my momma) these days…

Ok…getting back to work!

#DrContessa #married2med #happybirthday #motivation #better #me #respect #ancestors
